excerpt: Classic, seasonal Italian cuisine in a long-running venue with a laid-back vibe & a leafy courtyard.
detail_description: Guido's is a long-standing Italian restaurant in Cozumel known for its classic, seasonal Italian cuisine and laid-back atmosphere. Since opening in 1978, the restaurant has maintained consistency and evolved over the years. The chefs at Guido's blend French culinary skills with traditional flavors to create innovative dishes that please the palate. The menu features top-quality homemade Italian food, including fresh-made pasta, wood-fired pizzas, and their renowned seven-layer lasagna.
name: Guido's
address: Av. Rafael E. Melgar 23, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: If you're looking to take a break from the vibrant flavors of Mexican cuisine, Kooben Laab is a must-visit Italian restaurant nestled in Cozumel. This charming eatery has been delighting locals and visitors alike since 2018 with its freshly made bread and pasta, crafted right on-site. The inviting atmosphere, complete with warm decor and friendly staff, makes you feel like you're dining at a friend's home.
name: K'ooben Laab
address: Avenida Licenciado Pedro Joaquin Coldwell entre, Calle José María Morelos entre 25 y 39 numeo 533 a depto 2Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Seafood & cocktails served in a laid-back restaurant with views of a lush garden, plus live music.
detail_description: Casa Mission is a historic Mexican estate turned restaurant located in the heart of Cozumel. The lush garden and beautiful hacienda provide a picturesque backdrop for enjoying seafood, cocktails, and live music. The restaurant offers a diverse menu including vegan, vegetarian, and omnivore options for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. With its enchanting garden space and extensive menu featuring specialties like vegetable enchiladas and lime soup, Casa Mission promises an unforgettable dining experience.
name: Casa Mission
address: Av Lic Benito Juárez 55, Adolfo López Mateos, 77600 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Choza Cozumel is a popular family-run restaurant in Cozumel, known for serving authentic Mexican cuisine and regional specialties. The restaurant has a spacious interior suitable for larger groups and is open from breakfast to dinner. It's a place where you can enjoy traditional options like huevos rancheros or explore regional specialties such as huevos con chaya.
name: La Choza Cozumel
address: 10 Avenida Nte. # 216, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Burritos Gorditos is a small, family-owned joint in Cozumel known for serving some of the best burritos in the area. The authentic food is made with passion and served with Mexican flair. Fresh ingredients are combined to create savory dishes at reasonable prices. While burritos may not be traditional Mexican cuisine, this spot specializes in making delicious ones. The variety of fresh ingredients allows for options like vegetarian, egg and chorizo breakfast, and steak burritos.
name: Burritos Gorditos
address: 5a Av. Nte. S/N, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Cerveceria Punta Sur is a relatively new microbrewery in Cozumel, offering a refreshing break from the tourist crowds. It opened its doors in 2017 and has quickly become a favorite hangout spot for travelers seeking great craft beer and delicious food.
name: Cerveceria Punta Sur
address: 10a Avenida Sur 229, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Kinta Mexican Bistro, located on Ave. 5 between Calle 2 and 4, has quickly become a popular spot for modern Mexican cuisine. The restaurant features a small air-conditioned dining room and a charming garden area. It opens in the evening to cater to locals and tourists seeking an upscale dining experience after the departure of cruise ships.
name: Kinta Mexican Bistro
address: 5a Av. Nte. 148, entre 2 y 4, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Cocay is a popular restaurant in Cozumel that offers a diverse menu inspired by Mediterranean and Mexican cuisines. The woodfired pizzas, including the Pizza Cocay and Hawaiian, are favorites among patrons. In addition to pizza, guests can enjoy a variety of tapas such as goat cheese empanaditas, sauteed calamari, and sliced tuna sashimi.
name: La Cocay
address: Calle 8 Nte 208, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Pancho's Backyard is a popular upscale dining spot located in downtown Cozumel, offering delicious brunch and dinner options. The restaurant is known for its flavorful dishes, including the catch of the day and delectable dessert choices. In addition to its tasty brunch, Pancho's Backyard also serves up an array of cocktails, such as the renowned banana margarita.
name: Pancho's Backyard
address: Avenida General, Rafael E. Melgar & calle 8, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Casa Denis is a historic restaurant in Cozumel, Quintana Roo, offering some of the best Mexican food on the island. Established in 1946 and still managed by its original owners, it upholds the tradition of warm hospitality with a mantra of "Mi casa es su casa." Located near the main plaza, this cozy eatery serves Yucatecan specialties such as Cheese Empanadas and Yucatecan Poc-Chuc style pork chops.
name: Casa Denis
address: C. 1 Sur No. 132, Centro, 77600 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Candela is a popular dining spot in Cozumel, known for its authentic Mexican and Cuban-inspired cuisine. The restaurant recently relocated to a charming renovated home with a beautiful covered garden terrace. Open daily from 8 am to 5 pm, La Candela offers traditional Mexican breakfast dishes and serves delicious lunch specials at affordable prices. Visitors praise the restaurant for its flavorful guacamole, refreshing mojitos, and mouthwatering Cuban sandwich.
name: La Candela
address: 5a Av. Nte. Esquina calle 4 Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Monina is a popular beach-themed restaurant in Cozumel, known for its impressive breakfast menu and stunning views of the Caribbean. It's a favorite spot among locals for traditional Mexican and Caribbean cuisine, offering dishes like huevos rancheros and chilaquiles. The restaurant features a beach level area where you can enjoy drinks with your toes in the sand, as well as an authentic palapa deck upstairs to soak in the breeze.
name: La Monina
address: Av. Rafael E. Melgar s/n, Centro, 77600 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Taqueria El Pique is a popular spot in Cozumel, Mexico, offering authentic and traditional tacos with various fillings such as Al Pastor, Campechanos, Chorizo, and more. The restaurant also serves fajitas, frijoles, and cheese fondues at competitive prices. Despite its simple setting with limited seating in an open-aired dining area, the tacos are fresh, juicy, and perfectly grilled.
name: Taqueria El Pique
address: Pedro Joaquín Coldwell, 10 de Abril, 77622 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Ix Kool is a renowned restaurant in Cozumel that celebrates the rich Mayan heritage through its traditional gastronomic offerings. Chef Karla Enciso, recognized as one of the top 10 chefs in Quintana Roo, meticulously crafts authentic flavors and recipes based on extensive research into the culinary traditions passed down through generations in Mayan communities.
name: Ix Kool
address: Royal Village Shopping Center, Av. Rafael E. Melgar Local 53, 77675 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Maple Bakehouse is a popular coffee shop and bakery with three locations in Cozumel. They offer a wide range of meals throughout the day, catering to various dietary preferences including vegan, vegetarian, and gluten-free options. The bakery is known for its freshly baked breads and pastries, with occasional finds of gluten-free treats. Maple Bakehouse combines local and international flavors in their freshly made meals, satisfying hungry stomachs from morning until evening.
name: Maple Bakehouse
address: Calle 6 Nte 5A, entre Rafael Melgar y Calle Quinta Avenida, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Nestled on a sea cliff, Coconuts Bar & Grill is a popular spot offering a funky atmosphere and affordable drinks and food. It's known for drawing in diverse crowds and providing the perfect setting for engaging conversations over delicious margaritas. The bar also hosts full moon parties with live music, boasting awe-inspiring views of the moon rising over the ocean.
name: Coconuts
address: Carretera Costera Oriental, Km 43.5, 77645 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Rock 'n Java Cozumel Caribbean Bar & Grill is a popular spot located near the main cruise ship terminal in San Miguel. The restaurant offers a wide variety of American-style homemade food, including breakfast, lunch, and dinner. It's known for its hearty breakfast plates such as Belgian waffles, egg burritos, and steak and eggs. The exterior dining space is shaded by gazebos and the staff is welcoming to both locals and tourists.
name: Rock 'n Java Cozumel Caribbean Bar & Grill
address: Av. Rafael E. Melgar 602-C, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Nestled in the quiet streets of San Miguel, away from the typical tourist spots, La Perlita is a true hidden treasure. Specializing in lionfish, an invasive yet delectable species, this restaurant not only offers delicious seafood but also contributes to the local marine environment. The menu boasts a variety of seafood dishes such as coconut shrimp and grilled octopus. Its unpretentious and welcoming atmosphere makes it a favorite among locals and visitors alike.
name: La Perlita
address: Calle 10 Nte 499, Emiliano Zapata, 77620 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Inventive dishes served in a jungle-inspired restaurant with a thatched-roof hut & garden seating.
detail_description: Kondesa is a top dining spot in Cozumel, offering a refined gastronomic experience in a jungle-inspired setting. The restaurant features an open dining space with a romantic atmosphere and uses locally sourced products to create traditional Mexican dishes with modern twists. The menu focuses on meat and fish dishes of high quality. With its outdoor garden, Kondesa provides an upscale dining experience where guests can enjoy local and international cuisine under the stars.
name: Kondesa
address: 5a Avenida Sur 456, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: El Rincón de Addy is a charming breakfast spot located on a tranquil street, just a short walk from the town center. Originally situated in a plant nursery, it has now found its home on Calle Miguel Hidalgo. The restaurant offers a delightful array of flavors, including fresh juices, house-baked cakes, seasonal fruits, egg plates, and their renowned signature silver dollar hotcakes. The beautiful garden setting is adorned with plants and flowers that create a cozy atmosphere.
name: El Rincón de Addy
address: Calle Miguel Hidalgo, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Cuisine in Cozumel is a popular health food spot offering a variety of options for breakfast, lunch, and early dinner. The menu caters to vegans, vegetarians, and omnivores with an array of plant-based dishes such as fruit and smoothie bowls, tofu scrambles, vegan waffles and quesadillas, wraps, buddha bowls, fresh salads, entrees and healthy smoothies.
name: La Cuisine
address: Lic. Andrés Quintana Roo 100, Gonzalo Guerrero, 77660 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Restaurante Palmeras Cozumel is a popular spot located conveniently at the cruise port, making it a great place to relax and enjoy delicious food while taking in the stunning scenery. Since 1976, this restaurant has been attracting numerous visitors due to its prime location across from the Playa Del Carmen ferry pier. The menu offers a variety of options including well-prepared fresh fish fillets, tasty ceviche, and generous margaritas.
name: Restaurante Palmeras Cozumel
address: Ultramar, Av. Rafael E. Melgar 1, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Corazón Contento is a charming eatery located on 10 and 2, offering one of the best breakfasts in Cozumel. The cozy atmosphere and friendly staff make it a must-visit spot. Their menu features local dishes like Mayan huevos motulenos and Mexican breakfast enfrijoladas, both highly recommended. Guests rave about the delicious chilaquiles con pollo and the variety of salsas available.
name: Corazón Contento
address: Calle 2 Nte 160, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Chocolateria Isla Bella is a high-quality chocolate shop with unique flavors you won't find anywhere else. The owners are passionate about their product and it shows in the quality of the chocolate.
name: Chocolateria Isla Bella
address: Calle 4 Nte entre 5 y 10 Avenidas, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Al Pie del Carbon is a steakhouse with a wide range of choices on its menu. This restaurant has a great atmosphere, and the quality of the food is excellent. It's also close to the Boulevard, making it an easy option for lunch or dinner.
name: Al Pie del Carbon
address: Calle 3 Sur 98, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Alberto's Beach Restaurant is situated in the secluded southwest corner of Cozumel, offering a stunning beachfront setting. The restaurant is renowned for its delectable seafood, including grilled lobster tail, king crab, and mahi-mahi fish sourced directly from local fishermen. Its laid-back and casual atmosphere makes it the perfect spot to unwind after a day of swimming and sunbathing.
name: Alberto's Beach Restaurant
address: Carr. Costera Sur Km 18, 77687 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Colores y Sabores is a charming restaurant located on Calle 5, offering traditional Mexican dishes with a modern twist. The atmosphere is casual and laid-back, perfect for enjoying delicious homemade meals. Guests can choose between indoor and outdoor dining options while being serenaded by live Cuban music. The friendly staff and reasonable prices make it an ideal spot for both locals and tourists.
name: Colores y Sabores
address: C. 5 Sur 00020/000, entre AV RAFAEL E. MEL, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Generous lobster rolls, burritos & bowls are dished up in this compact, unpretentious venture.
detail_description: The Lobster Shack is a cozy, family-owned restaurant with a long-standing reputation for serving the freshest and highest-quality seafood on the island of Cozumel. Its unpretentious atmosphere makes it suitable for both romantic occasions and casual family meals. The restaurant has garnered a dedicated local following over the years, offering generous portions of lobster rolls, burritos, and bowls.
name: Lobster Shack
address: Calle 3 Sur, Local 2, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Located in Cozumel, Señor Frog's is a popular spot known for its lively and wild atmosphere. During the day, visitors can enjoy surprisingly good pub grub and flowing drinks while being entertained by the lively waitstaff. At night, the venue transforms into an Animal House ambiance with loud music, bar-dancing, bead-throwing, and balloon-hat-wearing revelry.
name: Señor Frog's
address: Avenida Rafael E. Melgar #551 local AD, 77675 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Le Chef Cozumel is a quaint, intimate continental restaurant located by the ferry terminal. The food is of high quality and reasonably priced, and the atmosphere is perfect for sharing a meal with good company. In the evening, choose from the ever-revolving list of daily specials.
name: Le Chef Cozumel
address: Av Rafael E Melgar 201 entre Calles 4, Calle 6 Nte y, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Restaurante El Moro is a beloved spot on the island, known for its homemade Mexican food and seafood. While it's a bit off the beaten path, locals and expats alike rave about its traditional Cozumel dishes, including flavorful mole options and the sought-after slow-cooked pork dish, Cochinita Pibil. The restaurant has recently relocated to a more central location in town, making it easier to access for those seeking an authentic culinary experience.
name: Restaurante El Moro
address: Av. Norte Por Calle 2, C. 75 Bis Avenida Nte., Emiliano Zapata, 77600 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: If you're on the hunt for authentic Mexican tacos, look no further than Guisados. This charming eatery is just a short stroll from the dock in the Centro area and offers an array of freshly made tortillas filled with delicious options like pork, beef, chicken, and vegetarian delights. The real magic happens when you customize your taco with their impressive selection of salsas and toppings.
name: Guisados
address: Av Lic Benito Juárez 254, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: El Pezcozon, located on 10th Avenue in Cozumel, is a popular seafood restaurant known for its fish tacos and Pulpo Ceviche. The menu features a variety of fresh seafood dishes based on traditional family recipes. This local gem is frequented by islanders and few tourists, offering an authentic Cozumeleno dining experience.
name: El Pezcozon
address: 40 Av.10 Norte 543, 40 Av. Nte 543, 10 de Abril, 77600 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Jolly is a great place for coffee and breakfast. The vibe is chill and friendly, the food is delicious, and it's easy to overlook. But don't miss out - it's worth a visit!
name: Jolly: Coffee And Late Breakfast
address: Calle 6 Nte 33, entre Rafael E Melgar y 5ta Avenida, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Novena Ola is a restaurant located on the first floor of the Museum of Cozumel, offering a fantastic view of the esplanade. The menu mainly features Mexican dishes and seafood, making it one of the best culinary experiences in Cozumel. With exclusively outdoor seating, it provides a cozy and romantic ambiance with excellent service.
name: Novena Ola
address: Museo de la Isla de, Av. Rafael E. Melgar 321-Planta Alta, entre calle 4 y 6 Norte, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: If you're a coffee aficionado visiting Cozumel, the COZ Coffee Roasting Company is an absolute must-visit. This charming café opens its doors bright and early at 6:30 AM, making it the perfect breakfast spot for those who rise with the sun. Nestled on Avenida 5 between Juarez and Calle 2, this local gem has gained popularity among both residents and tourists alike.
name: COZ Coffee Roasting Company
address: 5a Av. Nte. 50, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Located right on the pier in Cozumel, Three Amigos is a lively and welcoming restaurant with a party vibe. It offers traditional Mexican dishes like tacos, guacamole, quesadillas, and burritos as well as American fast food options such as cheeseburgers and chicken wings. The restaurant is highly recommended for its privileged location near the cruise port, making it a convenient stop for tourists. Guests can enjoy classic Tex-Mex cuisine while taking in views of the ships.
name: Three Amigos Cozumel
address: Puerta Maya, Carretera a Chankanaab, Carr. Costera Sur km 4.5, 77675 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Crazy King Burrito is a popular breakfast and brunch spot in Cozumel, offering a relaxing oceanfront dining experience. The menu features an array of lunch and dinner options, including tostadas, cocktails, and tasty tacos. Known for its generous portions and fresh ingredients, the burritos come in two sizes with various protein and veg combinations. The asada and shrimp burritos are particularly popular. Additionally, the restaurant offers a big vegan burrito for those with dietary preferences.
name: Crazy King Burrito
address: Calle 4 Nte s/n, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: "The Pub" is a popular spot known for its inviting outdoor garden dining area and delicious food. It's recommended to make reservations, especially during special occasions like St. Patrick's Day. The menu offers a variety of options, including burgers and traditional dishes like battered fish and chicken parm. Visitors have praised the quality of the food, with particular highlights being the perfectly cooked fish, flavorful chicken parm, and juicy bacon Bleu cheese burger. The fries are also highly regarded for their crispiness.
name: The Pub
address: 10a Avenida Sur 172, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Machete is a great mexican restaurant with friendly service and a real Mexican vibe. The chicken burrito is delicious and the guacamole is amazing!
name: Machete
address: Av. Doctor Adolfo Rosado Salas 221, Centro, 77665 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Sucre Sale is a French bakery and cafe that is famous for its desserts. The owner, Guillaume, and his wife Paula are friendly and always happy to chat with customers. The café has an easy-to-find location just a short walk from the ferry terminal on Calle 2 between 5th and 10th avenue. Along with delicious pastries, cookies, crepes, and pies, Sucré Salé also offers great coffee.
name: Sucré / Salé Café
address: Calle 2 Nte 101b, Centro, 77600 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Parrilla Mission, located on Ave Coldwell (also known as 30th) between Calles 2 & 4, is a restaurant owned by the same group that offers a wide variety of Mexican dishes, with a focus on tacos. The establishment serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Visitors can expect excellent food quality, very good service, and reasonable prices at this eatery.
name: Parrilla Mission
address: Calle 1 Sur por Av. 50 Sur, Adolfo Lopez Mateos, 77666 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Pescadería San Carlos is a hidden gem located in the mid-town part of San Miguel, Cozumel. Tucked away inside Bello Caribe Hotel & Suites, this quaint restaurant offers delicious and authentic Cozumel Caribbean style food with a Mexican "molcajete" flair. The restaurant is known for its incredible seafood, including fresh fish and mouthwatering ceviche.
name: Pescadería San Carlos
address: 50 Avenida Sur Bis, Adolfo López Mateos, 77667 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Del Sur Parrilla Argentina offers a delectable selection of empanadas, including savory options like beef, chicken, tuna, spinach, ham/cheese, cheese/bacon/plum or cheese and red sausage as well as sweet varieties filled with apples or caramel. The restaurant provides an inviting atmosphere with friendly and helpful staff. Diners can indulge in warm beef carpaccio and Angus rib-eye cooked to perfection. The burgers are consistently juicy and well-prepared for delivery orders.
name: Del Sur Parrilla Argentina
address: 5a Avenida Sur 299, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Casa Del Mojito is a small bar restaurant that offers Cuban-inspired mojitos and a variety of delicious food options. The owner prepares dinners to order, ensuring fresh and tasty meals for patrons. The menu features an array of mojitos to choose from, all highly recommended. Additionally, the friendly staff and excellent service make for a welcoming atmosphere.
name: La Casa Del Mojito
address: 5a Avenida Sur 201, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: If you're on the hunt for an unforgettable culinary experience in Cozumel, look no further than El Chino Marinero II. This gem is renowned for its mouthwatering fish tacos, which many claim to be among the best in all of Mexico. The restaurant also boasts a fantastic selection of ceviche that you simply can't miss during your visit. With a warm and welcoming atmosphere, you'll find genuine service and fair prices whether you're a local or just passing through.
name: El Chino Marinero II
address: C. 1 Sur 100, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Asteria Speakeasy Nightclub is known for its fresh seafood, sourced directly from the nearby waters. Located in Zona Hotelera Norte San Miguel de Cozumel, Quintana Roo, 77600, Mexico, it's considered the best speakeasy on the island.
name: Asteria Speakeasy Nightclub
address: 20 Av. Sur 965, Gonzalo Guerrero, 77664 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Popular delivery, carry-out & dine-in chain known for pizza, wings & pasta, plus sides & desserts.
detail_description: Pizza Hut is a well-known chain that offers delivery, carry-out, and dine-in options for pizza, wings, and pasta along with sides and desserts. In addition to its usual offerings, there's a Chinese restaurant called Chi's located on the second floor overlooking the ocean. Despite being crowded and noisy with only cash payments accepted in Mexican pesos, visitors were pleasantly surprised by the great pizza at an affordable price of $11. The crust was described as crispy yet fluffy while the toppings were generous.
name: Pizza Hut
address: Calle 3 Sur 81, Centro, 77668 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Guajillos Cocina Mexicana is a charming restaurant in Cozumel that offers an inviting atmosphere and exceptional service. The menu features authentic Mexican cuisine with daily specials, ensuring a delightful dining experience. The staff is accommodating to dietary preferences, including vegetarian options. Visitors can enjoy indoor or covered outdoor seating, along with delicious salsas and local prices.
name: Guajillos Cocina Mexicana
address: 85 avenida sur bis, entre calle 15 sur y calle 17 sur, 77660 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Paradise Beach Cozumel is a family-friendly, all-inclusive club offering a perfect beach and the largest heated swimming pool on the island. The entry fee covers food and drinks from two restaurants, as well as access to water activities like SUP boards, kayaks, and inflatable slides. The beach's clear waters and white sandy shores make it a top-rated destination for visitors.
name: Paradise Beach Cozumel
address: Carr. Costera Sur, Zona Hotelera Nte., 77687 Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico
